npc/guntur: The cruelest part is deeper in. When your own money runs out, the machine doesn't let you leave.
npc/guntur: It offers you more — loans, credit, "just enough to win it back." People borrow, and borrow again, and the debt is the whole point.
npc/guntur: I've watched homes sold out from under people who swore they had it under control. The loan is not a lifeline. There is nothing to win back. Do not take it.
